{"id":1080595,"date":[{"year":1997,"month":3,"day":3}],"page":"8","source":"","region":"","masthead":"教育园地","special_issue":"教育园地(第914期)","column":"名师讲台","genre":"","count":"2732","ytitle":"","mtitle":"谈高考英语复习","ftitle":"——语法之二","authors":["陈锡麟","周宁"],"text":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"陈锡麟　周宁"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"动词的时态、语态、语气是中学英语的重要内容。近年来的高考试卷中经常出现这方面的试题。略举几例:"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"1.-Oh，it＇syou!I__you.一Pvejusthadmyhaircut，andI＇mwearingnewglasses."},{"type":"paragraph","text":"A.didn＇trecognize　　　B，hadn＇trecognized"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"C.haven＇trecognized　D.don＇trecognize"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"试题的情景为一方一开始未认出对方。这是表示过去的动作，与现在无关，因此选项A为正确答案。"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"2.Whileshopping，peoples0met1mescan＇thelp——intobuyingsomethingtheydon＇treallyneed."},{"type":"paragraph","text":"A.topersuade"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"B.persuading"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"C.beingpersuaded"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"D.bepersuaded"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"根据题意，人们有时常被说服购物，表示的是被动意义，同时can＇thelp后接动名词，因此C为正确答案。"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"3.YesterdayJanewalkedawayfromthediscussion.Otherwiseshe——somethingshewouldregretlater."},{"type":"paragraph","text":"A.hadsald　B.said　C.mightsay　D.mighthavesaid"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"本题情景所表示的是含蓄的非真实条件，即Ifshehadnotwalkedawayfromthediscussion，因此D为正确答案。"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"为提高对这类试题的答题能力，考生必须准确掌握动词各类结构以及所表达的意义，同时通过分析题干所示的情景选择正确的动词形式。复习时应注意:"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"L动词各时态之间的区别。例如:"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"1wonderwhetherheeverwritesarriclesforthenewspaper.(经常的习惯)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Iwonderwhetherhehaseverwrittenarticlesforthenewspaperbefore.(过去的经历)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Afterthebui1dingofthebridge，thetowngrewrapidly.(表示过去的动作，与现在无关)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Sincethebuildingoftheundergr0undrailway，thetraffichasbeenlessheavy.(表示持续到现在的状态)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Hewasstillweakafteralongholiday。(表示过去的状态)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Theyhadbeengoodfriendsbeforetheirmarriage。(表示持续到过去某时间的状态)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"应注意时态的替代和呼应。例如:"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Itwilltakemelesstimetogotoworkwhenthelinewillbe0pentotrafficnextmonth.(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Itwilltakemelesstimetogotoworkwhenthelineisopentotrafficnextmonth。(√)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"时间状语从句中用一般现在时代替将来时。"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"We＇llstartatteniftherainwillstopbythattime。(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"——We＇llstartatteniftherainhasstoppedbythattime。(√)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"条件状语从句中用现在完成时代替将来完成时。"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"It＇snearly12:00，andJanestillhasn＇tcomehome。Isupposeshewillbehomes0on.(以“现在”为基点)——"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Hewasgoingtochecktheessayshisstudentshadwritten，buthisfr1endcame，sohehadtostopworking.(以“过去”为基点)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"2.动词语态的正确选择。例如:"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Weallsatisfiedwiththeteam＇sperformanceinthematch.(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Wewereallsatisfiedwiththeteam＇sperformanceinthematch.(√)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"(satisfy为及物动词“使……满意”，此处表示被动意义)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Good-lookingfoodisn＇talwaystastedgood.(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Good-lookingfooddoesn＇上alwaystastegood.(√)(连系动词不用于被动语态)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Thenewbornbabywasweighedthreekilos.(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Thenewbornbabyweighedthreekilos.(√)(weigh作“重若干”解为不及物动词，不用于被动语态)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"须注意某些特例中语态的使用。例如:"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Thiskindofworkbookisn＇tsoldwe1L(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Thiskindofworkbookdoesn＇tsellwell.(√)(sell作“有销路”解，不用于被动语态)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"要注意语态转换过程中被动语态的正确结构。例如:"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Thosemagazinesshouldhavetakenbacktothelibrary。(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Thosemagazinesshouldhavebeentakenbacktothelibrary。(√)(表示被动意义须用被动结构)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Abigposterwasputonthewall.(×)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Abigposterwasputuponthewal1.(√)(短语动词或介词动词转换时，不要漏遗副词或介词)"},{"type":"paragraph","text":"3.直陈语气和虚拟